Baxter, Appellant, v. Wesley, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

June 3, 1889.) Appeal from judgment on report of referee. Action by Algernon S. Baxter against Edward B, Wesley. *959Bedfleld & Lydeeker, for appellant. 5. & T. McMahon, for respondent. Per Curiam.

We have carefully examined the testimony in this case, and think it fully supports the findings of the learned referee who tried the case, and we think the reasons given by him in his opinion conclusive on the merits of the action. Judgment should be affirmed, with costs.
